The tension isn‚Äôt new, but it feels sharper now as stakes rise.

Builders are fine with tradeoffs. What‚Äôs missing isn‚Äôt alignment it‚Äôs leadership clarity. The hard part is building against shifting signals & changing priorities.

If DAU growth is the priority, that‚Äôs appreciated. But unclear signaling creates a bullwhip effect‚Äîteams make bets that get reversed by top-down shifts.

The decentralization crowd isn‚Äôt purity testing. Many are actively building infra for the distributed future. Without visibility into roadmap, governance, or decision-making (beyond dev calls), we‚Äôre outsourcing our futures & hoping there's green grass left to graze.

Things that might help:
‚Äì Clear protocol roadmap
‚Äì Defined boundaries: Apps vs Farcaster Protocol
‚Äì Transparency on FIP adoption vs ‚Äúteam priorities‚Äù
‚Äì Avoiding mid-flight rebrands

No one‚Äôs asking for perfection‚Äîjust predictability.
Let us build beside you, not beneath you.

Still bullish. Happy to help.
